Customer Relationship Management (CRM) System Using Agile
1. Introduction

Customer Relationship Management (CRM) is a software system used by organizations to manage interactions with customers, improve customer satisfaction, and increase business growth. The CRM system stores customer details, tracks communication, and helps in managing sales and support activities efficiently.

2. Objectives

To maintain customer records

To track customer interactions

To improve customer satisfaction

To support business decision making

3. Scope of the Project

The CRM system allows users to add, update, search, and manage customer data. It also supports interaction tracking and reporting features.

4. Agile Methodology Used

The Agile methodology follows an iterative development approach. The project is divided into small sprints, and each sprint delivers a working module of the system.

Agile Phases:

Requirement Gathering

Sprint Planning

Development

Testing

Review & Feedback

5. System Features

Customer data management

Interaction history tracking

Search and filter customers

User authentication

6. Advantages

Faster development

Easy to modify requirements

Continuous customer feedback

7. Conclusion

The CRM system developed using Agile methodology ensures flexibility, better customer management, and improved productivity.
